cs.NA, cs.SC, cs.SY, cs.LO, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is the most likely category as the paper deals with roundoff errors in numerical programs and proposes a framework based on optimization techniques. 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is also likely as the paper uses sums of squares certificates to provide formal roundoff error bounds for polynomial programs. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper mentions non-trivial programs from space control. 
- cs.LO (Optimization and Control) is relevant as the paper uses optimization techniques based on semidefinite programming. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with the efficiency and precision of the proposed tool.
